The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Memorable victories 
                                                   Memorable victories 
                      
	Following are some of the memorable victories by the national football team.         
	 1951: Asian Games, New Delhi, India bt Iran 1-0         
	 1952-55: India won the quadrangular meet         
	 1962: Asian Games Jakarta, India bt South Korea 2-1.         
	 2002: LG Cup, Ho Chi Minh City, India bt Vietnam 3-2         
	 2007: Nehru Cup New Delhi, India bt Syria 1-0         
	 2008: AFC Challengers Cup, Hyderabad/ New Delhi, India bt Tajikistan 4-1.         
	 2009: Nehru Cup, New Delhi, India beat Syria 6-5 via tie-breaker.         
	Note: India won the SAF Games 3 times, SAFF Cup 4 times.         
	 Bhutia is now the most successful India captain winning five trophies. He surpassed Sailen Manna, who won four trophies as the national skipper.           COMPILED BY HARI PRASAD CHATTOPADHYAY                                                                                                                   
